  "riddle": "1. Unearth the legacy of a fleeting vice as you seek the date when José María Reina Andrade first stepped into power in Guatemala.\n\n2. They say history is measured in days; calculate the passage of time from June 26, 1902, to March 15, 2026. What number of days does that reveal?\n\n3. In the realm of binary whispers, how many 1-bits illuminate the figure you uncovered in clue 2?\n\n4. Within the heart of Guatemalan governance lies a page that speaks of diverse tongues; how many languages are represented there?\n\n5. Seek the elevation upon which this congress stands — how high does it rise above sea level?\n\n6. What rating do the travelers bestow upon this seat of power? Search for their verdict on its quality.\n\n7. From the heights of clue 5, take the absolute difference between that value and the opinion from clue 6. What result emerges?\n\n8. If you were to traverse the landscape from a park enveloping Rock Creek to the Guatemalan legislative abode, how many minutes would your journey take by car?\n\n9. To find the final piece, add the values from clues 3, 5, 7, plus the travel time from clue 8, and combine those with 5. Then, compute the digital root of your total — what single digit do you obtain?",
